race.comment: Competitive sprint. ELENA MONTERO (9) is a fairly honest galloper resuming and is a fresh-up winner. When last resuming placed at Flemington. Looks well placed this level and should go close despite the wide draw. INFINITE MATRIX (2) has been building to a win, the latest finishing runner-up here over a little further when raced handy. Rates well on recent form and is among the chances. THUNDER AWARD (5) has missed the frame last couple but is going better than it looks. Has a big finish and looks well placed here, especially if there's pressure up front. Will be running on. AMINATU (7) returned from a break with a seventh over 1000m at Tatura but was only just over a length from the winner. Fitter and tends to run very well second-up.
